R Notebook

library(tidyverse)
library(tictoc)
library(caret)
library(ggfortify)
library(MASS)
library(cluster)
library(class)
source("./parameters.R")

Set the value of K

# choose among "complete", "single", "ward.D2", "centroid"
method = "centroid"

Open the data set

# Open the bag of words
fileName = "bow_tfidf__min_words_100_2grams_1000__sampling_balanced__cor_cut_0.01_from_1408_to_83_rm0.csv"
df = read_csv(fileName, col_types=col_types_df)
df = df[,-c(2,3,5:9)]
# During tests, we can work on a sample
sampled = TRUE
if (sampled == TRUE) {
  set.seed(42)
  max = nrow(df)
  sampled = round(max/10)
  df = df[sample(max, sampled), ]
}
# show the data set
df

Splitting the data

HC is a clustering technique so we can get ride of the train/test split and the labels.

X = df[,-c(1,2)]
X

Run HC

D = dist(X)
out = hclust(D,method = method)
plot(out)

Lets cut the tree and plot some points

# cut the tree
res = cutree(out,k=2)

# show the result
set.seed(42)
max = ncol(X)
sampled = 8
X_s = X[,sample(max, sampled)]
pairs(X_s,col=res,pch=19)
